summary: An Ordinance amending Section 12 of Ordinance No. 27323, entitled "An Ordinance relating to and providing for the licensing and regulating of the traffic in intoxicating and malt liquors within the City of Seattle, and providing penalties for violation thereof, and repealing Ordinance No. 16324, entitled "An Ordinance providing for the licensing and regulating of the traffic in intoxicating malt liquors within the City of Seattle and providing penalties for violation thereof", approved June 19, 1907; Ordinance No. 17789, entitled 'An Ordinance regulating the traffic in intoxicating and malt liquors within the City of Seattle on the day of any primary election, and providing penalties for violation thereof', approved January 21, 1908, and Ordinance No. 24657, entitled 'An Ordinance amending Section 16 of Ordinance No. 16324, entitled 'An Ordinance providing for the licensing and regulating of the traffic in intoxicating malt liquors within the City of Seattle, and providing penalties for violation thereof', approved June 19, 1907' approved July 25, 1910", approved May 31, 1911.
